Based on the retrieved memory, I will use Zellij layout files to define the session for the auth-refactor debugging session.

Here's a sample layout file that you can use:

```zellij
session auth-refactor-debugging {
    window main {
        pane top 30% {
            command tmux split-window -h
            command tmux select-pane -t 0
            command tmux send-keys "cargo run --bin auth-refactor -- --debug" Enter
        }
        pane bottom 70% {
            command tmux split-window -v
            command tmux select-pane -t 1
            command tmux send-keys "cargo run --bin auth -- --debug" Enter
        }
    }
}
```

This layout file sets up a two-pane window with the main pane running the `cargo run` command for the `auth-refactor` binary with the `--debug` flag, and the bottom pane running the `cargo run` command for the `auth` binary with the `--debug` flag. You can adjust the layout as needed to suit your preferences.

To use this layout file, save it to a file (e.g., `auth-refactor-debugging.zellij`) and then run `zellij --load-layout auth-refactor-debugging.zellij` to load the session.
